# GitHub Copilot Instructions for py-mcp Project
# This file contains instructions for GitHub Copilot to follow when generating code.

## Shell Environment
# Use git bash for all shell commands and scripts
# Commands should be compatible with bash.exe (Git Bash on Windows)

## Output Directory
# Generated documents should be saved to: generated/docs-copilot/
# Copilot will store all generated documentation in this subdirectory

## Code Style Guidelines
# Follow the project configuration in pyproject.toml for:
# - Line length: 100 characters
# - Python version: 3.8+
# - Code formatting: ruff format
# - Linting: ruff lint
# - Type checking: pyright

## Development Tools
# The project uses:
# - pre-commit hooks for code quality
# - markdownlint for Markdown files
# - ruff-format for Python code formatting
# - ruff for linting
# - pyright for type checking

## Project Structure
# src/          - Source code
# tests/        - Test files
# generated/    - Generated outputs
#   docs-copilot/ - Copilot-generated documentation

## Git Bash Requirement
# All shell scripts and commands must work with Git Bash (bash.exe)
# Avoid using PowerShell or Windows-specific commands
# Use forward slashes (/) for file paths

